results.name: Number of groups of order A128603(n).
comment: Number of groups whose order divides p^6 for p a prime.
The groups of these orders (up to A128603(54403784) = 1073741789 in version V2.13-4) form a class contained in the Small Groups Library of MAGMA. (corrected Mar 18 2007)
link: Klaus Brockhaus, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences related to groups
example: A128603(10) = 16 and there are 14 groups of order 16 (A000001(16) = 14), hence a(10) = 14.
program: (MAGMA) D:=SmallGroupDatabase(); [ NumberOfSmallGroups(D, n) : n in [ k: k in [1..455] | exists(t) {x: x in [t: t in [1..6] ] | IsPower(k, x) and IsPrime(Iroot(k, x)) } ] ];
xref: Cf. A000001 (number of groups of order n), A128603 (numbers dividing p^6 for p a prime), A098885 (number of groups of prime power orders).
results.author: _Klaus Brockhaus_, Mar 13 2007
